Now I can see the issue. In the `esp32s3_bringup.c` file, there's button initialization code at lines 514-520:

```c
#ifdef CONFIG_INPUT_BUTTONS
  /* Register the BUTTON driver */

  ret = btn_lower_initialize("/dev/buttons");
  if (ret < 0)
    {
      syslog(LOG_ERR, "Failed to initialize button driver: %d\n", ret);
    }
#endif
```

The issue is that `btn_lower_initialize()` likely opens file descriptors internally, and if it fails, those file descriptors are not properly closed. Let me check the button lower half driver implementation to understand the issue better.

